Class.name: Custom.SWARH.HIPS.ws.v2.q1.ItemNotFoundFault
Class.Description: <summary> Represents a fault when a specified item is not found in the HIPS database. </summary> Created from: http://sahipsh00.swarh.net:50500/HIPSServer_TEST/HIPS.Service.PCEHRService.svc?xsd=xsd14

Property.name: Identifier
Property.Description: <summary> Gets or sets the identifier value, if any, that was specified by the caller and was not able to locate the item. </summary>

Property.name: Qualifier
Property.Description: <summary> Gets or sets the qualifier, if any, that was specified by the caller and was not able to locate the item. </summary>

Property.name: Type
Property.Description: <summary> Gets or sets a code representing the type of item that was not found. Known examples are "Hospital", "Patient", "Episode" or "Address". </summary>
